article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 19, Northwestern St. 10
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Jeremy Moses threw two touchdown passes as Stephen F. Austin beat Northwestern State 19-10 on Saturday, clinching at least a share of the Southland Conference title. Moses finished 34-for-47 with 333 yards and an interception for the Lumberjacks (9-2, 6-1). Cordell Roberson caught seven passes for 128 yards and a score. The game was tied at 10 going into halftime, but the Lumberjacks scored nine unanswered points in the second half while holding the Demons (0-11, 0-7) scoreless to seal the win. Evan Engwall, who kicked a 29-yard field goal in the first quarter, connected from 33 yards out to put the Lumberjacks ahead 13-10 early in the third quarter. Moses threw a 57-yard TD pass to Roberson early in the fourth to give the Lumberjacks their final margin after a blocked extra point. Paul Harris threw for 261 yards and an interception for the Demons.
